  "text": "12 ''Often, [patients] are left to wonder if they are safe and who will be there for them when they need it most.'' 6(p.IX) These stressful experiences are accentuated by a persistent focus on disease, procedures, and treatments, rather than on the human experience of illness, hospitalization, and perceptions of feeling safe in a harsh environment. [CITATION_1] Nurses are in a unique position to effect change in hospital experiences and, ultimately, desired outcomes for hospitalized older adults.",
